&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Marketing Intern focused on Corporate Events, this role will play a key position in helping the marketing team plan, organize, and execute impactful company and customer events. This intern collaborate across marketing, sales, and operations to source top-tier venues, hotels, and vendors; manage event logistics and registrations; and keep complex projects running smoothly from start to finish. The marketing intern will assist in managing vendor communications before, during, and after events to ensure smooth execution and follow-up.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Duties and Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Source and request proposals from hotels, event venues, catering companies, transportation providers, and other vendors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in vendor selection, negotiation, and contract coordination to ensure high-quality event experiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist and maintain event registration systems, including attendee communications, data accuracy, and reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support project management of multiple concurrent events — tracking timelines, budgets, and deliverables.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support and organize logistics such as travel, accommodations, and transportation lists for attendees and staff.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain detailed event documentation, ensuring all moving parts are aligned across teams and vendors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with internal stakeholders to confirm event needs, branding standards, and guest experiences are met.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage vendor communications before, during, and after events to ensure smooth execution and follow-up.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with on-site event coordination and post-event reporting, including metrics and vendor feedback.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the Corporate Events team in developing materials and messaging to promote events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
